
= MakingSociety Podcast via http://makingsociety.com/2013/06/podcast-01-building-hardware-company/

=Description=

"about 40 minutes packed with advice, tips and resources to help you launch your open hardware business.

The unique goal of the monthly MakingSociety podcast is to help you go from maker to entrepreneur. We cover topics such as prototyping, manufacturing, distribution, raising money, product launching, licences and more.

In this first session, I interview Ben Einstein, co-founder of Bolt, the hardware incubator based in Boston. Passionate about creating great products and helping ambitious hardware companies, he talks about prototyping, design for manufacturing and products fitted for crowdfunding and open source."


